Ok I downloaded the file and I got a bunck of tda files or whatnot.  Could anyone clearly tell me what to do?

I would believe that the .tda files are openable from winRAR. they are winrar files, only the extension has been changed. They can still be openable from winrar, only Windows doesn't associate them directly to it.     So just open winrar, go to the download directory and click on one of the .tda files, and you should the option to extract whatever file (.iso or similar) is hiding within the archive.

I was stuck at compilerVfw.prm as well. It has something to do with codecs, so for me it helped to uninstall ACE megapack codecs and instead install a free codec-pack named Cole2k. I also upgraded to version 1.5.1 on Adobes homepage and installed a fix from Microsoft. Now it´s working just fine...

After a lot of searching I finally figured out how to install this and it works fine. For everyone else who has a hard time doing this: here's the idiot's guide to installing: 
1) open WinRAR and go to file>open archive 
2) select the folder where your files are in, change filetype "all files", now you see your files
3) select file with ending .001 and click open. now you see the .bin and .cue file. extract them somewhere.
4) open your burning software and open the .cue file there, burn on cd.
5) start installtion from cd, open the keygen from the crackfolder in the meantime
6) the keygen displays you one serial number at the top, enter it when the installtion process asks you for it. but leave it open while you continue.

7) installation finishes. when opening the program choose that you want to register it by phone, you see a reference number there. 
enter this into the keygen and then put the number the keygen gives you into Premiere's registration form. 

Done.
